{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/takeref()"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in order to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where the object that is being returned already exists).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the same ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"code":"g_object_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/takeRef()"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"takeRef()","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol"]]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol/takeRef()":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"type":"topic","title":"takeRef()","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/takeref()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/takeRef()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Object","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Object"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol","title":"ObjectProtocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"title":"ObjectRef","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"}}}